 varied everyday experiences, including negotiations of traditional gender norms, Shauna Pomerantz and Rebecca Raby show how teachers, administrators, parents, and media commentators can help smart girls thrive while working toward straight As and a bright future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aAcademic achievement. 0aGirlsxConduct of life. 0aGirlsxEducation. 0aSex differences in education. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aacademic success.  abelonging.  acollege.  aeducation.  aeducational philosophy.  aexclusion.  afeminism.  afeminist theory.  agender and women studies.  agender expectations.  agender studies.  agirls.  ahigh school.  ahigher education.  aintersectionality.  amicro resistance.  aneoliberal individualism.  aneoliberalism.  aperfection.  apost feminism.  arace and class.  asexism.  asocial aspects of education.  astress.  asuccess.  asupergirl.  atraditional gender norms.  awestern society.  awomen and girls.  ayoung adult.  ayoung girls.1 aHarris, Anita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaby, Rebecca, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052028414240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520959798?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520959798423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520959798/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY